Papirius Cursor is one of the favourite heroes os Roman tradition: his swiftness of soot, his strength, his capacities sor sood, and the iron strictness of his discipline, accompanied by occasioual touches os rough humour, made him as popular as Richard Coeur de Lion. His line of march was obviously through the Vestini aud along the coast of the Adriatic. How Publilius reached Apulia, Livy does not state clearly.
